CardDeck - Class in starvationevasion.sim
Each player region as a unique collection of 80 policy cards that make up that player's deck.

Each player's deck is shuffled at the start of the simulation.
CardDeck(EnumRegion) - Constructor for class starvationevasion.sim.CardDeck
Each player region has a unique deck to be read from .cvs file: playerRegion(String), card(String), count(int).

In future versions, players will be able to produce and save custom decks.

In this pre-test version, cards are just randomly picked with no difference for different player regions.

CleanRiverIncentivePolicy - Class in starvationevasion.common.policies
Title: "Clean River Incentive"

Game Text: "X% tax break for farmers in my region who reduce by Y% the outflow of pesticides and fertilizers from their farms into the rivers."

Draft Affects: When drafting this policy, player selects a percentage X [1% through 100%] and Y% [1% through 100%].

Votes Required: Automatic

Model Effects: The sim estimates the number and location of farms within the region and the amount spent by those farms on improved irrigation.

CovertIntelligencePolicy - Class in starvationevasion.common.policies
Title: "Covert Intelligence"

Game Text: "You get to covertly examine target player\'s hand and the top two cards of that player\'s deck. You may target yourself. During the voting phase, other players will see that you have played this card, but not know its target. Bonus: If you can correctly answer a hidden research question, you examine the top seven cards of the target player\'s deck."

Votes Required: Automatic

Model Effects: The fact that such cards as this exist, implies the draw pile must be set at the start of the game rather than cards being randomly picked at draw time.
